Using MR cholangiopancreatography to reveal anomalous pancreaticobiliary ductal union in infants and children with choledochal cysts. The purpose of this study was to determine whether MR cholangiopancreatography can accurately depict anomalous pancreaticobiliary ductal union in children with choledochal cysts.Twenty children (age range, 1 month-13 years mean age, 4.6 yearsThe type of choledochal cyst (type Ia, n = 4 type Ic, n = 7MR cholangiopancreatography provides diagnostic information about anomalous pancreaticobiliary ductal union in children with choledochal cyst.